From Stephen Guerke Subject Re How can I use the mouse in NON Windows applications under MS WINDOWS In article Apr ucsu Colorado EDU gonzaled ucsu Colorado EDU LGV MC writes One addition to this I don't know if it applies to everybody For my Microsoft dpi mouse to work with windowed DOS apps, I had to use the driver that came with Windows Version didn't allow me to do it for some reason For Logitech rodents use the lmouse driver that comes with windows also you need to be using a video driver that supports use of the mouse, both the VGA and SUPERVGA that come with Windows will support it both of these are color drivers, if you're lucky the manufacturer of your video card might have a driver that is compatable and will support a mouse Steve Stephen Guerke, Coord Computer Resources University of Delaware Parallel Program Georgetown, DE ILV UDELVM UDEL EDU